entries.name: L1Staking
entries.description: Contract keeping track of stakers which act as sequencers/proposes. It is responsible for stakers registering and withdrawals and for verifying BLS signatures of stakers (currently not implemented).

entries.name: L1ETHGateway
entries.description: Contract used to bridge ETH from L1 to L2.

receivedPermissions.description: Actors allowed to commit transaction batches and propose state roots

entries.name: L1MessageQueueWithGasPriceOracle
entries.description: Contains the array of queued L1 -> L2 messages, either appended using the L1Messenger or the EnforcedTxGateway.

entries.name: ZkEvmVerifierV1
entries.description: Current SP1 verifier using Blobs for DA.

entries.name: L1StandardERC20Gateway
entries.description: Contract used to bridge ERC20 tokens from L1 to L2. It uses a fixed token list.

entries.name: MultipleVersionRollupVerifier
entries.description: Used to update the verifier and keep track of current and old versions.

receivedPermissions.description: Actors allowed to commit transaction batches and propose state roots

entries.name: L1GatewayRouter
entries.description: Main entry point for depositing ETH and ERC20 tokens, which are then forwarded to the correct gateway.

entries.name: MorphRollup
entries.description: The main contract of the Morph chain. Allows to post transaction data and state roots, implements challenge mechanism along with proofs. Sequencing and proposing are behind a whitelist.

receivedPermissions.description: Actors allowed to commit transaction batches and propose state roots
can pause and unpause, override any batch, revert batch, update proof window, update challengers, modify verifiers
Actors allowed to commit transaction batches and propose state roots

entries.name: EnforcedTxGateway
entries.description: Contracts to force L1 -> L2 messages with the proper sender. Currently paused: true.

entries.name: L1CrossDomainMessenger
entries.description: Contract used to send L1 -> L2 and relay messages from L2. It allows to replay failed messages and to drop skipped messages. L1 -> L2 messages sent using this contract pay for L2 gas on L1 and will have the aliased address of this contract as the sender.

entries.name: ZkEvmVerifierV1
entries.description: SP1 verifier using Blobs for DA (being deprecated).

entries.name: Whitelist
entries.description: Contract implementing a generic whitelist. Currently used to define the actor that can relay the L2 basefee on L1.
